    <h1>Hu&#xAD;man health and po&#xAD;ten&#xAD;tial</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20201212/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-12-12"><time>2020-12-12</time></a>
        - <span>THE BIG STORY</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>• On top of safe­guard­ing pub­lic health and mak­ing head­ways in ther­a­peu­tics and med­i­cal tech­nolo­gies, the na­tion wants to im­prove qual­ity of life.</p>
    <p>We as­pire to de­velop new ap­proaches that can help Sin­ga­pore­ans lead longer and health­ier lives, and adapt more ef­fec­tively to changes to the life and work par­a­digm, and for older in­di­vid­u­als to main­tain their phys­i­cal and cog­ni­tive well­ness.</p>
    <p>MR LAWRENCE WONG, Min­is­ter for Ed­u­ca­tion and co-chair of the Multi-ministry Task­force on Covid-19.</p>
    <p>Ex­am­ple: Grow­ing Up in Sin­ga­pore To­wards Healthy Out­comes or Gusto (A study by KK Hos­pi­tal, A*Star and Na­tional Univer­sity Health Sys­tem)</p>
    <p>• Sin­ga­pore’s largest birth co­hort study en­rolled over 1,200</p>
    <p>Sin­ga­porean women since it was ini­ti­ated in 2009.</p>
    <p>• The study tracked the par­tic­i­pants since their early preg­nancy, and will con­tinue to study their chil­dren, through­out their growth from in­fancy to their early ado­les­cence.</p>
    <p>• In­sights from the study have helped to shape Sin­ga­pore’s health poli­cies, such as uni­ver­sal screen­ing for ges­ta­tional di­a­betes mel­li­tus for all preg­nant mums.</p>
    <p>• In 2025, the re­search will study the chil­dren’s phys­i­cal, so­cio-emo­tional and cog­ni­tive devel­op­ment in their ado­les­cent years, which can help re­searchers iden­tify fac­tors for op­ti­mal devel­op­ment to help them achieve a higher qual­ity of life.</p>

